When working in [Preferences][prefs-tidyoptions] you may sometimes find it
convenient to reset all of default options to Tidy’s built-in “factory settings”
without resorting to [deleting all of your preferences][defaults_delete].


<div class="steps" markdown="1">

1. Access the menu at the bottom of the **Tidy Options** panel in the
   Preferences window.
   <% if target_feature?(:feature_exports_config) %>
   ![options context menu][context-options-prefs-pro]
   <% else %>
   ![options context menu][context-options-prefs]
   <% end %>

2. Select **Reset options to factory defaults**.

3. You should see that all of the Tidy options have reverted to their factory
   default states.

